raw_data.title: Project Manager II
raw_data.description: The Project Manager (PM) II manages the full lifecycle of complex software and system development projects. Ensures projects are completed on-time, within budget, and in accordance with client requirements. Organizes project through the development of a project plan. Leads teams and allocates resources. Develops schedules with key milestones, identifies risks, and develops contingency plans. Establishes work plans and staffing for each phase of the project and oversees recruitment activities. Ensures projects are completed according to specifications. Responsible for proper project documentation. Ensures quality and productivity standards are maintained while meeting project/client deadlines and budgets. Provides interface to the customer and other project leads. Performs a Quality Assurance (QA) role. Reviews proposals and participates in contracts negotiations. Responsible for training new personnel.

raw_data.description: The Subject Matter Expert (SME) I provides expert support, analysis, and research into complex processes relating to the subject matter.
